<sect1 id="GetColumnMapping">
  <!-- DNT-Start --><title>GetColumnMapping</title><!-- DNT-End -->

  <!-- DNT-Start --><para><emphasis>result</emphasis> <emphasis role="bold"> :=
  STD.File.GetColumnMapping<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.File.GetColumnMapping</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>File.GetColumnMapping</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>GetColumnMapping</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis> <emphasis> file </emphasis> <emphasis
  role="bold">);</emphasis></para><!-- DNT-End -->

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start --><emphasis>file</emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry>A null-terminated string containing the logical
          filename.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->Return:<emphasis> </emphasis><!-- DNT-End --></entry>

          <entry><!-- DNT-Start -->GetColumnMapping<!-- DNT-End --> returns a null-terminated string containing
          the comma-delimited list of field mappings for the
          <emphasis>file</emphasis>.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>The <emphasis role="bold"><!-- DNT-Start -->GetColumnMapping<!-- DNT-End --> </emphasis>function returns
  the field mappings for the <emphasis>file</emphasis>, in the same format
  specified for the SetColumnMapping function.</para>

  <para>Example:</para>

  <!-- DNT-Start --><programlisting format="linespecific">Maps := STD.File.GetColumnMapping('Thor::in::SomeFile');
</programlisting><!-- DNT-End -->
</sect1>
